which food can you give to a hedgehog one has wandered into our garden i heard either dog or cat food thanks for any help do not give milk to hedgehogs as it gives them diarrhoea and they can die from malnutrition supplement their diet with cat or dog food small pieces of meat or chicken and even crushed peanuts in small amounts there's a great website that explains a hedgehogs natural diet and then gives advice on what you can and can't feed them its great that you are helping to feed the hedgehogs in your garden http www thehedgehog co uk diet htm Cat Hedgehog Breastfeeding Domestication Chocolate Vegetarianism Livestock Soybean Food Fancy rat Crohn's disease Taboo food and drink Omega-3 fatty acid Sonic the Hedgehog Nutrition Veganism Agriculture Chicken Diarrhea Cat food Garfield Animal rights Carnivore Kitten Atkins Nutritional Approach Cuisine of Africa RuneScape quests Dog Cuisine of the Philippines Chao (Sonic the Hedgehog) Egg (food) Dieting Domestic rabbit Saturated fat Cuisine of Malaysia Potassium Guinea pig Cuisine of Denmark Peanut butter Vegetarian cuisine Cuisine of the Southern United States Dim sum Factory farming Vitamin C Milk Raw food diet Cuisine of Brazil Irish cuisine Minor characters in Sonic the Hedgehog Protein Healthy eating Scurvy Tofu Hunting Jewish cuisine Trans fat Food allergy Tooth Dog food Albatross Pig Vitamin D Malnutrition Fecal incontinence Peruvian cuisine Chili con carne Vegetarian nutrition Sonic the Hedgehog (16-bit) Biological pest control Ramen Episodes of Lost (Season 2) Chronic fatigue syndrome Stomach cancer Pet skunk Soy milk Famine Organic food Miles "Tails" Prower Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Hypomagnesemia Curry Japanese cuisine Chaos Emerald Chicken soup Taikyoku shogi Inuit Hamburger Organic farming Elephant Anemia Bovine spongiform encephalopathy Environmental vegetarianism Food guide pyramid Trailer Park Boys People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals French fries Echidna Aztec 